review_title: 1 out of 3 for a high price
review_content:
Best Blush Ever. Very flattering. The color is a nice shade for fairer skin and has a beautiful luminosity. The bronzer is barely there but borderline orange. I have no idea who it would work for. It's too warm for fair skin (no matter your undertone) and not pigmented enough for the palest spectrum of medium. I use it as a crease color on "no makeup" makeup days just to use it. The highlighter? It's chunky glitter that doesn't stick. I don't prefer a glittery highlight but I could have used this as an eyeshadow topper if it had any stick. You need a glitter glue to get this to do anything. Even then it's patchy and glitter without much of a sparkle. It is literally the worst highlighter I've ever owned. I could almost forgive the crappy bronzer and highlighter for the beautiful blush that smells like peaches but for the price.....no.

product_name: Too Faced Sweet Peach Glow Peach-Infused Highlighting Palette
user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Medium', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
I am absolutely obsessed with this palette. I want to start off by saying that I have a medium skin tone, and all the products are perfect shades for me. I wish Too Faced would come out with a darker palette for those with deeper skin tones, because people shouldn't have to miss out on this. It also smells like peaches (if you are sensitive to scents) but the smell dissipates once it's on the face. I will go from the products left to right. Highlighter- Very shimmery. Not subtle, but not crazy intense either. I do like it, but I don't use it as much as I should. Blush- This has a very nice sheen, but it's in no way glittery or shimmery. It has a buildable color, so you can customize how pigmented you want it to be. It gives a very natural flush and a glow from within look. Bronzer- I actually finished THE ENTIRE thing. That has never happened to me before where I love a product that much. It is the right amount of cool and warm toned. It has a slight sheen, so it is not matte, but it is not shimmery either. All in all, I highly recommend this palette.
